article.headline: FIU 58, Stephen F. Austin 56
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- DeJuan Wright scored 18 points as Florida International defeated Stephen F. Austin 58-56 in the Lumberjack E-Tech Classic on Sunday. Dominique Ferguson added 13 points and Jeremy Allen 11 for the Panthers (3-6). Phil Taylor's 3-pointer with 1:51 remaining gave Florida International a 58-54 lead. Jereal Scott responded with a jumper for the Lumberjacks (4-4), but they got no closer, missing three shots in the final eight seconds. Scott had 15 points and eight rebounds for Stephen F. Austin. Antonio Bostic added 13 points and Jonathan King 10.
